# FreshLens — Database & RLS

Applies when editing `infra/db/`.

## Every migration that adds a business table must include

1. `tenant_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES tenants(id)`
2. `ALTER TABLE ... ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`
3. Policy using `current_setting('app.tenant_id')::uuid`
4. Index on `tenant_id` for tenant-scoped queries

## Example pattern

```sql
CREATE TABLE scans (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  tenant_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES tenants(id),
  image_path TEXT NOT NULL,
  classification TEXT,
  freshness_score REAL,
  model_version TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

ALTER TABLE scans ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

CREATE POLICY tenant_isolation ON scans
  USING (tenant_id = current_setting('app.tenant_id', true)::uuid);
```

## Rules

- Serialize DB migrations — one PR at a time for schema changes
- @buwaneka-halpage must approve all `infra/db/` PRs
- Add or extend RLS isolation test in CI when migrations land
